[8/8] The CR contains the most comprehensive #PBM reform we’ve ever seen and patients will see lower prices at the counter because of it. I will support this package on the floor and thank @SpeakerJohnson & @SteveScalise for standing up to the PBM lobby on behalf of patients.

[7/8] The State Strategic Stockpile Act extends the authorization for a program supporting states in developing their own medical stockpiles for use in case of a public health emergency or a major disaster or emergency declared by the President.

[6/8] The Telehealth Modernization Act extends Medicare telehealth flexibilities. Telehealth is a vital tool for seniors and those in rural areas to access quality care, and we must ensure this flexibility is protected.

[5/8] The NO PBMs Act will codify existing requirements that plan sponsors work with any willing pharmacy that meets their standard contract terms, and those terms must be reasonable and relevant. It will increase access to the most trusted health care professionals, pharmacists.

[4/8] The PBM Accountability Act will promote price transparency for prescription drugs by employer health plans by requiring PBMs to be HONEST. It also ensures that patients receive a summary regarding their plan’s prescription drug spending. Competition reduces prices.

[3/8] The Protecting Patients Against PBM Abuses Act will delink PBM compensation from the cost of medications and increase transparency. This will eliminate incentives for the middlemen to inflate drug costs to line their own pockets, & the savings will be passed on to patients.

[2/8] The Drug Price Transparency in Medicaid Act will ban “spread pricing” for seniors. This will ensure pharmacies are fairly and adequately reimbursed for serving Medicaid beneficiaries, and savings will be passed on to patients.
